Congratulations.

19
00:02:34,260 --> 00:02:34,760
Lu Chen.

20
00:02:40,380 --> 00:02:42,510
Congratulations on getting married.

21
00:02:42,930 --> 00:02:45,060
Congratulations on getting married.

22
00:03:17,410 --> 00:03:19,320
You're taking a flight immediately after getting married?

23
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:21,100
Your wife didn't try to stop you?

24
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:21,740
She's sad,

25
00:03:22,850 --> 00:03:24,050
but she won't stop me.

26
00:03:32,380 --> 00:03:33,300
Lu Yanchen, Captain of the Third Brigade

27
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:34,850
of the SWAT Detachment of Tianwen City,

28
00:03:34,850 --> 00:03:35,980
reporting for duty.

29
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:37,200
Lu Yanchen.

30
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:39,840
Welcome.

31
00:03:43,060 --> 00:03:44,920
I have good news. Guess what it is.

32
00:03:45,420 --> 00:03:46,620
I don't want to guess.

33
00:03:48,380 --> 00:03:48,840
Tell me.

34
00:03:49,370 --> 00:03:50,900
What's the secret mission?

35
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:54,260
Captain Lu is assisting at Gonghai for a month.

36
00:03:54,260 --> 00:03:55,260
He's very near us.

37
00:03:55,390 --> 00:03:56,160
Great!

38
00:03:56,510 --> 00:03:57,820
Let's visit him this weekend.

39
00:03:57,820 --> 00:03:59,160
No need to wait for the weekend.

40
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:00,180
The team there is newly established.

41
00:04:00,180 --> 00:04:01,060
They're short of manpower.

42
00:04:01,060 --> 00:04:01,620
I've assigned you

43
00:04:01,620 --> 00:04:02,160
there

44
00:04:02,620 --> 00:04:03,550
to work with him.

45
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:04,160
Good.

46
00:04:20,339 --> 00:04:21,000
Captain Lu.

47
00:04:24,530 --> 00:04:25,990
You’ve all met Captain Lu.

48
00:04:26,020 --> 00:04:27,930
I don't have to introduce you again.

49
00:04:27,930 --> 00:04:29,590
Captain Lu, here is the thing.

50
00:04:29,630 --> 00:04:30,020
They've set up

51
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:31,270
a base station here.

52
00:04:31,610 --> 00:04:32,350
Yesterday, they dug up many bombs like this

53
00:04:32,350 --> 00:04:33,780
left behind by the war

54
00:04:33,780 --> 00:04:35,240
at the construction site.

55
00:04:35,390 --> 00:04:36,690
We've surveyed the area.

56
00:04:36,690 --> 00:04:38,420
There are many bombs like this.

57
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:40,350
A civil explosives company like ours

58
00:04:40,350 --> 00:04:41,570
should be able to handle this.

59
00:04:41,570 --> 00:04:42,100
However,

60
00:04:42,730 --> 00:04:44,050
the terrain here is complicated.

61
00:04:44,050 --> 00:04:44,630
That's why

62
00:04:44,630 --> 00:04:46,230
we've invited you to help us.

63
00:04:47,050 --> 00:04:48,010
Let's go in and take a look.

64
00:04:48,010 --> 00:04:49,340
Okay. This way, please.

65
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:50,170
Look.

66
00:04:54,570 --> 00:04:54,930
Here.

67
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:58,970
Hello, Mr. Shen.

68
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:02,060
Captain Lu.

69
00:05:02,770 --> 00:05:03,100
Look.

70
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:04,250
These...

71
00:05:05,290 --> 00:05:06,130
These bombs

72
00:05:06,570 --> 00:05:08,100
are all awaiting disposal.

73
00:05:08,520 --> 00:05:09,650
Considering that

74
00:05:10,050 --> 00:05:10,970
accumulating too many explosives

75
00:05:10,970 --> 00:05:11,730
here

76
00:05:11,730 --> 00:05:12,810
might be dangerous,

77
00:05:12,810 --> 00:05:13,970
we should transport them away

78
00:05:13,970 --> 00:05:15,990
once we reach a certain number of them.

79
00:05:15,990 --> 00:05:17,300
There are so many bombs.

80
00:05:17,300 --> 00:05:18,910
The climate here is unpredicatable.

81
00:05:18,910 --> 00:05:20,330
We must install a lightning protection system nearby

82
00:05:20,330 --> 00:05:21,460
as soon as possible.

83
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:22,220
Captain Lu.

84
00:05:22,330 --> 00:05:23,610
You are truly a professional.

85
00:05:23,610 --> 00:05:24,340
Don't worry.

86
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:26,480
I've made all the arrangements.

87
00:05:26,740 --> 00:05:27,770
Let's take a look outside.

88
00:05:27,770 --> 00:05:28,220
Okay.

89
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:48,640
These bombs

90
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:50,170
are all of different types.

91
00:05:50,290 --> 00:05:51,159
There are different

92
00:05:51,159 --> 00:05:51,690
cautionary measures

93
00:05:51,690 --> 00:05:53,220
when handling each of them.

94
00:05:54,170 --> 00:05:54,960
For example,

95
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,420
the fuze of this bomb is at the top.

96
00:05:57,840 --> 00:05:59,490
There's a primer at the base of that bomb

97
00:05:59,490 --> 00:06:00,600
for launching,

98
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,390
but it also has a fuze

99
00:06:02,690 --> 00:06:03,570
at the top.

100
00:06:03,930 --> 00:06:05,150
Moreover,

101
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:06,280
the anti-tank and anti-personnel mines

102
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:07,080
we saw just now

103
00:06:07,610 --> 00:06:08,770
must all be handled carefully.

104
00:06:08,770 --> 00:06:09,170
Yes.

105
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:10,210
That's why we asked

106
00:06:10,210 --> 00:06:11,450
your team for help.

107
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:13,130
However,

108
00:06:13,410 --> 00:06:15,490
the SWAT team here is newly established.

109
00:06:15,490 --> 00:06:16,450
I'm the only experienced member

110
00:06:16,450 --> 00:06:18,720
of the Explosive Ordnance Disposal Team.

111
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:20,050
There are so many bombs.

112
00:06:20,290 --> 00:06:20,950
I'll go back

113
00:06:21,050 --> 00:06:23,000
to discuss this with my commanding officer

114
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:23,890
and request additional manpower.

115
00:06:23,890 --> 00:06:24,530
Okay.

116
00:06:25,730 --> 00:06:26,390
Captain Lu,

117
00:06:27,010 --> 00:06:27,890
the diagrams you provided us with

118
00:06:27,890 --> 00:06:28,930
last time

119
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:30,330
were immensely helpful.

120
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:32,700
Now that we are collaborating again,

121
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,659
I must learn all I can from you.

122
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:35,210
Mr. Shen,

123
00:06:35,610 --> 00:06:36,409
your opinions

124
00:06:36,690 --> 00:06:38,020
are as valuable as mine.

125
00:06:38,810 --> 00:06:40,120
Captain Lu, go check out

126
00:06:40,120 --> 00:06:41,340
the accomodations.

127
00:06:41,490 --> 00:06:42,770
Our company set it up.

128
00:06:42,930 --> 00:06:44,560
We will be eating and living together

129
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,560
like colleagues.

130
00:06:45,650 --> 00:06:46,640
Yes, Captain Lu.

131
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:48,010
We cleared a room for you

132
00:06:48,010 --> 00:06:49,210
in the workers' dorm.

133
00:06:49,390 --> 00:06:51,060
The living arrangements are not ideal.

134
00:06:51,060 --> 00:06:51,730
I'm sorry.

135
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:52,400
Not at all.

136
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:53,610
I'll ask the team

137
00:06:53,610 --> 00:06:54,930
to send the people and things here.

138
00:06:54,930 --> 00:06:55,290
Sure.

139
00:07:14,310 --> 00:07:15,670
Let me tell you a secret.

140
00:07:17,490 --> 00:07:18,220
What secret?

141
00:07:19,610 --> 00:07:20,760
I'm married.

142
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:24,710
It's legal.

143
00:07:25,050 --> 00:07:26,310
We have a certificate.

144
00:07:26,450 --> 00:07:27,650
When did this happen?

145
00:07:27,730 --> 00:07:28,860
A couple of days ago.

146
00:07:30,210 --> 00:07:31,360
I couldn't hold it in anymore.

147
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:32,490
I finally said it.

148
00:07:32,770 --> 00:07:33,830
I haven't told anyone before.

149
00:07:33,830 --> 00:07:35,290
It was like a secret affair.

150
00:07:35,290 --> 00:07:36,610
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

151
00:07:36,610 --> 00:07:37,680
I'll buy you a big meal.

152
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:38,940
How about lunch today?

153
00:07:39,210 --> 00:07:40,810
All you care about is eating.

154
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:42,030
Work is hard.

155
00:07:42,159 --> 00:07:44,220
Only eating can relieve our worries.

156
00:07:45,350 --> 00:07:46,210
How do you feel?

157
00:07:47,290 --> 00:07:48,690
How do I feel?

158
00:07:51,290 --> 00:07:52,820
I feel a sense of belonging,

159
00:07:52,970 --> 00:07:53,890
the kind of contentment that comes

160
00:07:53,890 --> 00:07:55,770
after everything has settled.

161
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,130
The feeling of home?

162
00:07:58,700 --> 00:07:59,830
The feeling of home.

163
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:06,530
What are you looking at?

164
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:08,890
I want to see what's different

165
00:08:08,890 --> 00:08:10,150
about a married woman.

166
00:08:11,370 --> 00:08:13,530
What is it?

167
00:08:14,930 --> 00:08:15,920
Nothing yet.

168
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:18,880
You are still so young and beautiful.

169
00:08:45,010 --> 00:08:45,670
Captain Lu.

170
00:08:46,770 --> 00:08:48,010
Are you calling your partner?

171
00:08:48,010 --> 00:08:48,370
Yes.

172
00:08:49,010 --> 00:08:51,410
I'm making use of the free time while we eat.

173
00:08:51,450 --> 00:08:53,010
Say hello to your partner for me.

174
00:08:53,010 --> 00:08:53,340
Okay.

175
00:09:34,450 --> 00:09:34,920
Excuse me.

176
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:35,650
My husband is calling.

177
00:09:35,650 --> 00:09:36,800
I'll take it outside.

178
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:38,080
Take care of her for a moment.

179
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:38,770
I didn't expect you

180
00:09:38,770 --> 00:09:39,700
to be so whipped.

181
00:09:40,090 --> 00:09:41,490
Just call him back later.

182
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:42,650
Yes.

183
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:43,850
You should let men

184
00:09:43,850 --> 00:09:45,130
feel anxious.

185
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:48,160
His situation makes it troublesome for him to call.

186
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:50,160
Enjoy your meal. I'll be right back.

187
00:09:50,210 --> 00:09:51,870
Her husband's job must be really special.

188
00:09:51,870 --> 00:09:54,070
He doesn't even have time to make a call.

189
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:55,480
I heard her father's company

190
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:56,450
is a publicly listed company.

191
00:09:56,450 --> 00:09:56,880
He's probably

192
00:09:56,880 --> 00:09:58,410
from a similar background.

193
00:09:58,640 --> 00:09:59,440
You're wrong.

194
00:09:59,810 --> 00:10:01,570
Her husband is a SWAT officer.

195
00:10:01,930 --> 00:10:03,330
He does explosive ordnance disposal.

196
00:10:03,330 --> 00:10:05,250
There is no cell phone reception

197
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:06,710
at his latest assignment.

198
00:10:06,970 --> 00:10:08,010
Every time he wants to make a call,

199
00:10:08,010 --> 00:10:08,960
he has to drive out

200
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:11,330
at least 5 kilometers to get cellular signal.

201
00:10:11,330 --> 00:10:12,770
Apparently, he often calls from mountains.

202
00:10:12,770 --> 00:10:13,590
The signal gets blocked

203
00:10:13,590 --> 00:10:15,190
every time a cloud passes by.

204
00:10:15,460 --> 00:10:16,920
It's not easy to make a call.

205
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:18,920
He can't call from his place of work?

206
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,720
SWAT teams work at the front line

207
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:22,650
and there is always risk of danger.

208
00:10:22,700 --> 00:10:24,360
It's beyond our imagination.

209
00:10:27,290 --> 00:10:28,950
Did you climb a mountain today

210
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:30,650
or are you with the team?

211
00:10:31,290 --> 00:10:32,750
The weather is nice today.

212
00:10:33,010 --> 00:10:34,010
I'm on a mountain.

213
00:10:37,620 --> 00:10:39,100
Is it hot over there?

214
00:10:40,460 --> 00:10:42,060
It's getting hot these days.

215
00:10:45,830 --> 00:10:47,560
Long time no see. Do you miss me?

216
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:51,010
Yes.

217
00:10:53,410 --> 00:10:55,070
But there's nothing we can do.

218
00:10:55,460 --> 00:10:56,810
We might only get to meet again

219
00:10:56,810 --> 00:10:58,970
in the middle of summer.

220
00:10:59,490 --> 00:11:00,050
Yes.

221
00:11:01,170 --> 00:11:02,210
There have been some emergencies

222
00:11:02,210 --> 00:11:03,820
at the new city.

223
00:11:04,570 --> 00:11:06,320
The original timeframe of the mission

224
00:11:06,320 --> 00:11:07,410
may be delayed.

225
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,460
It'll take a long time.

226
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:16,360
Hello?

227
00:11:27,890 --> 00:11:29,200
What mountain are you on?

228
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,380
The signal is so bad.

229
00:12:14,140 --> 00:12:15,840
How many days of annual leave do you still have?

230
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:16,500
All of them.

231
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:18,280
Do you want to go on a trip?

232
00:12:18,530 --> 00:12:18,960
Where?

233
00:12:19,340 --> 00:12:19,870
Gonghai.

234
00:12:20,390 --> 00:12:22,050
You want to find your husband?

235
00:12:22,610 --> 00:12:24,470
You don't want to see Captain Qin?

236
00:12:25,280 --> 00:12:25,920
Why would I

237
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:27,480
want to see him?

238
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:28,730
You work so hard

239
00:12:28,730 --> 00:12:29,610
looking after his child

240
00:12:29,610 --> 00:12:30,560
all the time.

241
00:12:30,650 --> 00:12:32,170
You must have so much to say to him.

242
00:12:32,170 --> 00:12:33,530
You've overestimated me.

243
00:12:33,530 --> 00:12:34,520
I'm always cold

244
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:35,650
towards strangers.

245
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:36,770
You two

246
00:12:36,770 --> 00:12:38,300
are not strangers anymore.

247
00:12:38,370 --> 00:12:40,090
You call each other every week.

248
00:12:40,090 --> 00:12:43,240
You're very good friends.

249
00:12:43,490 --> 00:12:44,250
Not really.

250
00:12:44,690 --> 00:12:46,350
We only talk about education.

251
00:12:46,430 --> 00:12:47,710
That's fine.

252
00:12:48,330 --> 00:12:49,790
You've never been married,

253
00:12:49,790 --> 00:12:52,200
but you're turning into a parenting expert.

254
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:53,330
Are you going or not?

255
00:12:53,810 --> 00:12:54,330
I...

256
00:12:54,850 --> 00:12:55,850
Let me hesitate for a few seconds.

257
00:12:55,850 --> 00:12:56,160
One.

258
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:57,570
Two.

259
00:12:58,330 --> 00:12:58,810
Three.

260
00:12:58,810 --> 00:12:59,410
I'm going.

261
00:12:59,610 --> 00:13:00,210
I'm going.

262
00:13:00,550 --> 00:13:01,070
Happy?

263
00:13:01,810 --> 00:13:02,920
That's right.

264
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:03,600
Come on.

265
00:13:04,230 --> 00:13:05,490
I'm worried about you.

266
00:13:05,690 --> 00:13:07,090
I have to take care of you.

267
00:13:07,430 --> 00:13:08,310
Thank you.

268
00:13:09,200 --> 00:13:10,570
It's great there.

269
00:13:10,570 --> 00:13:11,630
You will definitely like it there.

270
00:13:11,630 --> 00:13:13,130
You won't be disappointed.

271
00:13:13,130 --> 00:13:15,520
Besides, Gonghai is very near Qining.

272
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:16,900
It's only half an hour by car.

273
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:19,210
Let's take time off and go on holiday there.

274
00:13:19,210 --> 00:13:21,480
I'll think about it.

275
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:22,660
Don't.

276
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:23,640
It's settled.

277
00:13:41,810 --> 00:13:42,210
Hello?

278
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:43,640
I'm lucky.

279
00:13:44,170 --> 00:13:45,500
I suddenly got a signal.

280
00:13:46,850 --> 00:13:48,040
I'll visit you next week.

281
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:50,100
It's dangerous if you run around now.

282
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:51,170
What danger?

283
00:13:51,170 --> 00:13:52,230
I can't tell at all.

284
00:13:52,380 --> 00:13:53,180
It's settled.

285
00:13:54,490 --> 00:13:54,890
Hello?

